install grainmodel
==================

wajig install python-pexpect python-pyparsing python-syck gmsh python-tables swig libmesh0.6.0-pure-dev python-petsc tetgen

./setup build
./setup.py install --prefix=$HOME/lib


usage
=====

input is the geometry in mesh/t.geo

./fem

output is the solution in tmp/so.pos
and gradient in tmp/sog.pos

./show

to clean everything
===================

./clean

Documentation
=============

In the doc directory (see README there) to compile the tex sources.
